  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Coat the <strong>chicken breasts</strong> with the <strong>ground cumin</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597161635779-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597161635779-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597161635779-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597161635779-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597161635779-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and top with a large knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the corn until tightly sealed and add to a baking tray lined with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the corn is tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597161646766-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597161646766-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597161646766-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597161646766-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597161646766-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breasts</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned, then remove from the heat</p><p>Whilst the chicken is browning, add the <strong>saffron</strong> to 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>hot</strong> <strong>water</strong> and set aside to infuse – this is your <strong>saffron liquid</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597161670738-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597161670738-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
